{
  "texts": [
    "For instance, Gkillas et al. (2020) suggest examining the macrofinancial determinants of crypto market jumps, and Grobys and Huynh (2022) propose assessing the impact of jumps in stablecoins.",
    "Gkillas et al. (2022) suggest assessing the impact of cryptocurrencies and the jumping behavior of other financial assets (upside, downside, and large and small jumps).",
    "Finally, volatility forecasting requires models with different data frequencies.",
    "The in-sample and out-ofsample forecasts can be reconciled at the short-, medium-, and long-term horizons.",
    "Studies have identified various factors and developed different models or approaches that can predict cryptocurrency prices, challenging the efficient market hypothesis (all information is already reflected in prices)."
  ]
}